  "prompt": "So I might be asking a silly question, but how do I view the source of a cookie?",
  "response": "To view the source or details of a cookie, you can use different methods depending on your browser:\n\n1. Chrome/Edge:\n- Open Developer Tools (F12 or Right-click > Inspect)\n- Go to the \"Application\" tab\n- Select \"Cookies\" in the left sidebar\n- Click on the specific domain to see cookie details\n\n2. Firefox:\n- Open Developer Tools (F12 or Right-click > Inspect)\n- Go to the \"Storage\" tab\n- Select \"Cookies\" in the left sidebar\n\n3. Safari:\n- Enable Developer menu in Preferences > Advanced\n- Open Web Inspector (Develop > Show Web Inspector)\n- Go to the \"Storage\" tab\n\n4. Using Browser Settings:\n- Chrome: Settings > Privacy and Security > Cookies and other site data\n- Firefox: Options > Privacy & Security > Cookies and Site Data\n\n5. Programming Methods:\n- JavaScript: `document.cookie`\n- Browser Extensions like \"EditThisCookie\"\n\nEach method will show cookie properties like name, value, domain, expiration, etc.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these methods?",
